  "prompt": "How early can you check in at the airport for international flight?",
  "response": "The recommended check-in time for international flights varies by airline and airport, but generally:\n\n1. Most airlines allow check-in 3-4 hours before an international flight.\n\n2. Some airports and airlines may permit check-in up to 5-6 hours before departure.\n\n3. Specific check-in times can depend on:\n- Airline policies\n- Airport regulations\n- Destination country requirements\n\n4. Recommended earliest check-in times:\n- Typically 3 hours before international flight departure\n- For larger, busier airports, arriving 4 hours early is sometimes suggested\n\n5. Factors to consider:\n- Time needed for security screening\n- Passport and visa checks\n- Potential lines and crowds\n- Baggage drop-off procedures\n\nAlways check with your specific airline and airport for their exact check-in policies and recommended arrival times.",
